Package: assignmentb2
Title: Count Missing Values for All Columns by Group
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Zoe", "Horlick", email = "zoehorlick@icloud.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Given a data frame `data` and a column `group`, `count_all_missing_by_group()` creates a new data frame with one row per level of `group`. The first column of the output data frame contains the levels of `group`, and the rest of the columns contain the number of missing values for all columns in `data` except `group`.
